Heat salt in a large non-stick skillet over high heat. Add ground pork, onion, chili powder, garlic, and pepper. Cook and stir 8 minutes. Add undrained pinto beans, Nakano(R) Seasoned Rice Vinegar - Original, and 1/4 cup water. Cook and stir 10 minutes. Wrap ground pork in tortillas. Serve with garnishes, as desired.